citeinfo.title: Wastewater Land Application Sites for Idaho

descript.purpose: Geographically represent the locations of wastewater land application sites for the State of Idaho's environmental programs. Additionally for ground and surface water quality reporting.
descript.supplinf: Originally developed as a potential contaminant in the Source Water Protection project.

dataqual.logic: Data was digitized using ArcGIS polygon editing tools. There are no line intersections. All the data are isolated enclosed polygons. There are no line duplications.
dataqual.complete: Historical HMU data is expected to be included in the near future.

procstep.procdesc: Data was digitized on-screen using existing hard-copy maps (from permits) and either DOQQ (when available) or SPOT 10m satellite imagery (when DOQQs were not available).
